========================================================================
ARCHITECTURE NOTES FOR NEXT AGENT
========================================================================

Key design decisions and gotchas:

1. MPAS stream manager only supports nCells/nEdges/nVertices decomposed
   dims. Remapped (lon,lat) output MUST bypass stream manager via direct
   PIO. This is by design.

2. PIO decomposition type MUST match Fortran array type. PIO_REAL requires
   real(4). Mismatch produces garbled output with NO runtime error.

3. apply_masked packs validity mask as level numlev+1 in the same send
   buffer. ONE alltoallv + ONE SpMV handles both field and mask.
   Normalizes by valid_frac (weight sum of valid sources only), not frac_b.

4. Fortran sequence association: when passing array(pcols,nlev) to a
   subroutine declaring dummy(ncol,nlev) with ncol<pcols, the dummy
   array's stride doesn't match the actual array's stride at levels k>1.
   ALWAYS pass explicit sections array(1:ncol,:) when ncol may differ
   from the first dimension of the actual array.

5. MPAS framework calls AM init twice (setup + compute_on_startup).
   register_var has a duplicate-name guard to handle this.

6. Fill value flow: AM sets fillValue (1e34) at source → remap caller
   detects (MPAS_OCN_FILL*0.1 threshold or exact cam_fillvalue match)
   → zeros field + sets mask=0 → apply_masked normalizes by valid_frac
   → output SHR_FILL_VALUE (1e20) where valid_frac < epsilon.
   _FillValue attribute in output file = real(SHR_FILL_VALUE, 4).

7. Map file uses global cell IDs (n_a = N_total = 465044 for IcoswISC30E3r5),
   not ocean-only indexing. The gcol_to_ocean_col identity branch is taken.
